This software needs the Java and it’s JavFX library installed on your machine to compile and run.

This project relies on JavaFX to function correctly. You'll need to have JavaFX installed to compile and run the application.
﻿﻿﻿Download JavaFX: Head over to the official JavaFX website and download the latest version suitable for your operating system.
﻿﻿﻿Install JavaFX: Follow the installation instructions provided on the JavaFX website. Make sure you have the JavaFX SDK set up properly on your machine.
﻿﻿﻿Configure Your Environment: Add the JavaFX SDK to your system's PATH or configure your IDE to include JavaX libraries. This will ensure that the application can find JavaFX when building and running.
